---
import Layout from '@layouts/Layout.astro';
import Footer from '@components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Support | Last Time I"
  description="Get help with the Last Time I iOS app."
>
  <main class="page-wrap">
    <a href="/lasttimei" class="back-link">&larr; Back to Last Time I</a>

    <h1>Support</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Need help? We're here for you.</p>

    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>How do I add a new item to track?</h3>
      <p>Tap the "+" button in the top right corner of the home screen. Enter a name for your task and select a category, then tap "Add Item".</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>How do reminders work?</h3>
      <p>Open any item and scroll to the "Reminder" section. Choose how many days you want to wait before being reminded. You'll receive a notification if you haven't marked the item as done within that time period.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>What do the colors mean?</h3>
      <p>Colors indicate how long it's been since you completed a task:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Green:</strong> Done within the last 7 days</li>
        <li><strong>Yellow:</strong> Done 7-30 days ago</li>
        <li><strong>Orange:</strong> Done 30-90 days ago</li>
        <li><strong>Red:</strong> Done over 90 days ago or never</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Where is my data stored?</h3>
      <p>All your data is stored locally on your device. Nothing is sent to any server. If you delete the app, your data will be deleted as well.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Does this app require an internet connection?</h3>
      <p>No. Last Time I works completely offline. There are no accounts, no cloud sync, and no servers. Everything runs on your device, so you can use the app anywhere, anytime.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>How do I delete an item?</h3>
      <p>Open the item you want to delete and tap the "Delete" button at the bottom of the screen.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-item">
      <h3>Can I recover deleted items?</h3>
      <p>No, deleted items cannot be recovered. Please be careful when deleting items.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>If you have questions, feedback, or need help with something not covered above, please reach out:</p>
    <p><a href="mailto:amanmittal.work@gmail.com">amanmittal.work@gmail.com</a></p>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style is:global>
  body {
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, #d4f5dd 0%, #eefaf1 35%, #ffffff 100%) !important;
  }
</style>

<style>
  .page-wrap {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 40px 24px 40px;
    font-family: "Helvetica Neue", Arial, sans-serif;
    color: #1d1d1f;
  }

  .back-link {
    display: inline-block;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: #6e6e73;
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  .back-link:hover { text-decoration: underline; color: #1d1d1f; }

  h1 {
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 6px;
    letter-spacing: -0.3px;
  }

  .subtitle {
    color: #6e6e73;
    font-size: 15px;
    margin: 0 0 32px;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 32px 0 12px;
    color: #1d1d1f;
  }

  .faq-item {
    border: 1px solid #d2d2d7;
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 16px 20px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    background: #fff;
    box-shadow: 0 1px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04);
  }

  .faq-item h3 {
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 700;
    margin: 0 0 6px;
    color: #1d1d1f;
  }

  .faq-item p {
    margin: 0;
    color: #6e6e73;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .faq-item ul {
    margin: 8px 0 0;
    padding-left: 18px;
    list-style: disc;
  }

  .faq-item li {
    color: #6e6e73;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }

  p {
    color: #6e6e73;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  a {
    color: #30D158;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  a:hover { color: #28b84c; }
</style>
